messages.content:
Hi, 
I have created a ZkProgram which generates a proof that is verified in a Smartcontract. But when sending the transaction to the local Mina, I always get `Invalid proof for account update?`
I reduced the problem to a small code sample, hopefully some can give some input, probably has something to do with the local mina, because it generates the transaction proof without problems
<https://gist.github.com/rpanic/994be1a67a25ebf214b48e10081fc9f8>
@gregor @Florian
I think this might (still) be due to a bug that was fixed a while ago but not yet supported in SnarkyJS because that would make SnarkyJS incompatible with Berkeley
the fix for that should be available again once Berkeley is redeployed
I'll check nonetheless, maybeits something different
Is there a PR open for which I can try it out?
the bindings with the fix should be on `mina/develop`
Alternatively, to unblock you, you could simply disable proofs for now
Actually those bindings should be on snarkyjs/berkeley
Okay, this error happens in both 0.7.3 and 0.8.0
yeah, that makes sense because we didn't merge develop / berkeley for this release. will do for the next one though, which will correspond to a network restart
@rpanic @gregor has this issue been resolved or still a WIP?
